      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">28.307</ph> Insurance under cost-reimbursement contracts.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
         <p id="d1860e8" class="- topic/p ">Cost-reimbursement contracts (and subcontracts, if the terms of the prime contract are extended to the subcontract) ordinarily require the types of insurance listed in <xref href="28.307-2.dita#FAR_28_307_2"
                  base="i1087951"
                  outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                  class="- topic/xref ">28.307-2</xref>, with the minimum amounts of liability indicated. (See <xref href="28.308.dita#FAR_28_308"
                  base="i1087963"
                  outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                  class="- topic/xref ">28.308</xref> for self-insurance.)</p>
      </conbody>
